# Observability conventions

## Prometheus

- Counters/histograms live in `MetricsService` (`prom-client`). Reuse labels: `scenario_runs_total{type,status}`, `scenario_run_duration_seconds{type}`, `http_requests_total{method,path,status_code}`.
- Expose scrape at **`GET /metrics`** (no `/api` prefix). Register new domain metrics in the same registry, not ad-hoc endpoints.

## Logs (Loki)

- Scenario logs go through **`ScenarioLogService`** (pino JSON). Every run must emit at least one line with **`scenarioType`**, **`scenarioId`**, **`duration`**, and **`error`** when applicable. Keep `app: "signal-lab"` in the base object.
- Prefer `context: "scenario"` on scenario lines so Grafana/Loki queries stay simple.

## Sentry

- Initialize only when `SENTRY_DSN` is set. Use `Sentry.captureException` for unhandled/demo server errors (e.g. `system_error` scenario). Optional breadcrumbs for client-side validation paths.
